    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "SEATTLE, Nov. 9.-The Atlas\nLumber & Single Co. in it's suit\nagainst the Great Northern railway\nin the federal court has filed 16 af-\nfdavits charging discrimination by\nthe road in the matter of supplying\ncars. The affidavit Of Everett\nGriggs, vice president of the ST.\nPaul G. Tacoma Lumber Co.\ncharges that the railroad has been\nholding cars for three and four\ndays at Tacoma, awaiting oriental\nshipments, and refusing to allow\nthese cars to be used by the local\nlumbermen."
    }
  ]
